Operatives of the Rivers State Police Command has arrested the chairman of Gokana local government area, Hon. Paul Kobani, for alleged being the prime sponsor of the late most wanted kidnapper, Honest Digbara, popularly known as Boboski. Boboski was arrested last weekend by a combined team of the Nigeria Police Force and a local vigilante outfit, at Korokoro-Tai in Tai local government area of the state. He died hours after he was paraded before newsmen at the police headquarters in Port Harcourt. A source at the police headquarters told LEADERSHIP Weekend that upon his arrest, the late wanted kidnapper had made some revelation linking some prominent politicians in Ogoniland to his activities.